# Dart Coding Standards

## General Guidelines
- Follow the [Dart Style Guide](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart/style)
- Use `camelCase` for variables and functions
- Use `PascalCase` for classes and enums
- Use `snake_case` for file names

## Project-Specific Standards
- Use `setState` for state management initially (not BLoC or other complex patterns)
- Use `SharedPreferences` for data persistence
- Do not use external fonts or image assets
- Do not use `freezed` package or `part` syntax
- Do not implement account functionality
- Do not use `cached_network_image` package

## Documentation
- Add documentation comments for all public APIs
- Use /// for documentation comments
- Include parameter descriptions for functions

## Testing
- Write unit tests for utility functions and services
- Write widget tests for UI components

Always follow these standards to maintain code quality and consistency.